Foreign Key Concept

Foreign Key usedto enforce database integrity. 
Foreign Key in one table points to primary key in another table.
Foreign key constrain prevents invalid data form being inserted into foreign key column.

Altert table ForeignKeyTable add constraint ForeignKeyTable_ForeignKeyColumn_FK
ForeignKey (ForeignKeyColumn) reference PrimaryKeyTable (PrimaryKeyColumn)

Query:-
Alter table tblPerson add constraint tblPerson_GenderID_FK
ForeignKey (GenderID) refernces tblGender (ID)
